        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 29 at 7:44PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 744 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Walcott, or over Crowleys Ridge State Park, moving northeast at 15
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Paragould, Crowleys Ridge State Park, Lake Frierson State Park, Oak
Grove Heights, Fontaine, Evening Star, Walcott, Beech Grove,
Stanford, Light, Walnut Corner, Bethel, Finch, Lorado, Herndon,
Faulknerville, Noxburn, Goobertown, and Crowley's Ridge State Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
